                                div.header Team "J" The First
                                div.meta Marian Styer, Joyce Chen, James Payor, Beckett Colson
                                div.description
                                  | Tensegrity Robot: He dances! Made primarily of acrylic, fishing line,
                                  | rubber bands, and pure unadulterated passion, this is one coordinated 
                                  | fellow! He's even controlled by the Myo Armband!
                        
                        div.title 
                          div.ui.middle.aligned.grid
                            div.row
                              div.three.wide.column
                              div.ten.wide.center.aligned.column
                                h3 Firefly
                              div.three.wide.right.aligned.column                          
                                i.dropdown.icon
                        div.content
                          div.ui.items
                            div.item
                              div.ui.medium.image
                                img(src="{% static 'images/firefly_01.jpg' %}")                              
                              div.content
                                div.header Team Glastonbury Landscaping LLC
                                div.meta Michelle Qiu, Robert Rudolph
                                div.description
                                  | FireFly is a lightbulb that can change warmth to adjust to a room's 
                                  | lighting needs. During the day, FireFly can be set to produce bright 
                                  | natural sunlight. At darker hours, FireFly throws a soft, warm glow
                                  | that is friendlier on your eyes. Just like F.lux, for real life.
                                  | A rotating collar at the base adjusts the warmth.
                        
                        div.title 
                          div.ui.middle.aligned.grid
                            div.row
                              div.three.wide.column
                              div.ten.wide.center.aligned.column
                                h3 Handheld CNC Plotter 
                              div.three.wide.right.aligned.column                          
                                i.dropdown.icon
                        div.content
                          div.ui.items
                            div.item
                              div.ui.medium.image
                                img(src="{% static 'images/cnc.jpg' %}")                              
                              div.content
                                div.header Team Autoplots
                                div.meta Marshall Craft, John La, Jack Erdozain, Elliot Owen, Jimmy Mawdsley
                                div.description
                                  | CNC Drawing Robot, takes in vector files and traces over drawing. 
                                  | Tracks motion so it can be shifted over and continue drawing if you want 
                                  | to draw something larger than its range of motion.
                        
                        div.title 
                          div.ui.middle.aligned.grid
                            div.row
                              div.three.wide.column
                              div.ten.wide.center.aligned.column
                                h3 Mesh-Network Gamma Spectrometer 
                              div.three.wide.right.aligned.column                          
                                i.dropdown.icon
                        div.content
                          div.ui.items
                            div.item
                              div.ui.medium.image
                                img(src="{% static 'images/gamma.jpg' %}")                              
                              div.content
                                div.header Team MakeRadiation
                                div.meta Jake Hecla, Danielius Kramnikius, Caitlin Fischer, Han Zhang, Banti Gheneti
                                div.description
                                  | Our device is designed to quantify and identify distributed radioisotope 
                                  | contamination from a wide variety of sources. This approach avoids risk
                                  | to civil/military personnel and vastly improves the ability to manage
                                  | evacuation routes and prioritize resources in response to nuclear disaster.
                                  | In comparison to most radiation-measurement beacons, these devices have
                                  | the ability to discriminate between various radioisotopes using a compact
                                  | gamma spectrometer. The devices are low-cost, and can be deployed en masse
                                  | via an air-drop over the target zone. Each device communicates its data
                                  | through a mesh network to a master unit, which uploads it to a webserver.
                        
                        div.title 
                          div.ui.middle.aligned.grid
                            div.row
                              div.three.wide.column
                              div.ten.wide.center.aligned.column
                                h3 Rhyno 
                              div.three.wide.right.aligned.column                          
                                i.dropdown.icon
                        div.content
                          div.ui.items
                            div.item
                              div.ui.medium.image
                                img(src="{% static 'images/rhyno.jpg' %}")                              
                              div.content
                                div.header Team Rhyno
                                div.meta Ahmet Can Musabeyoglu, Birkan Uzun, Wegene Tadele
                                div.description
                                  | We are building a Cheap, Compact and Easy to Use ring called Rhyno that 
                                  | detects simple gestures like swiping up, down, left and right as well
                                  | as zooming in and out. It achieves this by making use of accelerometer
                                  | and gyroscope sensor data. The ring also uses Bluetooth LE to communicate
                                  | with any Bluetooth LE enabled devices and control them.
                        
                        div.title 
                          div.ui.middle.aligned.grid
                            div.row
                              div.three.wide.column
                              div.ten.wide.center.aligned.column
                                h3 Securidesk 
                              div.three.wide.right.aligned.column                          
                                i.dropdown.icon
                        div.content
                          div.ui.items
                            div.item
                              div.ui.medium.image
                                img(src="{% static 'images/securidesk2.jpg' %}")                              
                              div.content
                                div.header Team Crimson45
                                div.meta Fiorella Vargas, Jessica Lam, Joy Hui, John Holland
                                div.description
                                  | Pressure sensitive mat that can be activated/deactivated using RFID. 
                                  | When change in pressure is detected, alarm sounds, lights turned on,
                                  | and user is sent an alert via email. Applications are for security
                                  | of personal belongings when taking breaks (bathroom, food run, short
                                  | walk or meeting) when working at library, cafe, dining hall etc.

    
